indicator.description:
1.Notification rate of new ss+ TB cases: New smear positive TB, cases notified to the National Health authorities   during a specified period  per 100 000 population;

2.Treatment success rate: new smear positive TB cases; new smear positive TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed) among new smear positive TB cases notified;

3.Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: TB cases (all forms) notified to the national health authorities during a specified period per 100 000 population.

4.Treatment success rate, laboratory confirmed  New MDR-TB cases: laboratory confirmed new MDR TB cases successfully treated ( cured plus completed)  among those enrolled in second-line treatment during  the year of assessment

target.comment:
1. Notification rate of SS+ forms of TB cases: 29 cases per 100,000 population;
2. Treatment success rate of new SS+ forms: 81%, 2013 cohort;
3. Notification rate of all forms of TB cases: 85 cases per 100,000 population;
4. Treatment success rate of MDR-TB cases: 80%.

indicator.description:
-National Human Rights Action Plan approved;
-National Institute of Democracy and Human Rights under the President of Turkmenistan  effectively monitors Turkmenistan's international obligations in the sphere of human rights, National Human Rights Action Plan and Universal Periodic Review  implementation and efficiently exercises its mandate;
-Awareness of goverment bodies, public organizations, general public about human rights. Public organizations take part in discussions on National Human Rights Action Plan implementation. Capacity of national trainers strengthened.
-Recomendations of options for National (Representative) Offices for Human Rights/National Representatives for Human Rights prepared.

baseline.comment:
-National Human Rights Action Plan in development;
-Existing/current capacity National Institute of Democracy and Human Rights;
-Limited awareness of public and goverment officials about human rights and regarding Turkmenistan's international obligations in the field of human rights.
-Limited experience in the field of National (Representative) Offices for Human Rights/National Representatives for Human Rights and in the area of constitutional reforms in Turkmenistan

target.comment:
-National Human Rights Action Plan  approved and implemented;
-Strengthened Turkmen National Institute of Democracy and Human Rights capacity to implement and monitor Turkmen's obligations in the field of human rights;
-Awareness of public and goverment officials about human rights and in respect of Turkmenistan's obligations increased. Public organizations take part in National Human Rights Action Plan discussion and implementation. Train for Trainers group's capacity increased.
-International experience of options for National (Representative) Offices for Human Rights/National Representative for Human Rights examined and recommendations prepared. International experience in the field of constitutional reforms researched.

actual.comment:
- Inception workshop was conducted on 18-19 Nov., 2015;
- Inception report is developing;
- AWP for 2016 has been developed;
- Project registered;
- Study Tour was organized;
- Topographic map of Green Polygon will be done in 2016;
- Reports on Kaakha and Green Polygon are developing by international experts.

indicator.description:
-A design for an inclusive model to facilitate PWDs to participate in vocational training courses completed, in keeping with the revised legislation;
-The existing 10 month vocational training programme, conducted by the Ministry of Textiles reviewed and revised together with Ministry of Education and included an inclusive model ensuring of PWDs have been accommodated;
-The Ministry of Textile has prepared the necessary training materials and processes according to the revised curriculum, to accommodate potential PWDs in the 10 month training;
-Targeted PWDs have submitted applications to the textile 10 month vocational course and have received assistance throughout the course.
